		<p>	In traditional Jewish culture physical competency and sports were not highly valued. Physical exercises were seen as goim naches (entertainment of non-Jews). Instead, learning and Talmud knowledge were valued. The ideal of male beauty was a student of the yeshiva (yeshiva bocher), who from a young age studied books. This ideal of the delicate and learned man was repeated in literature, arts, and popular culture. </p>
		<p>Zionism, which became one of the ideologies of nationalism in Europe at the end of the 19th century, played the largest role in the transformation of views about the Jewish male body. The ideology of the nation-state was accompanied by the exclusion of minorities and, for Jewish communities, anti-Semitism. The Zionist movement proposed not only the creation of an Israeli government in Palestine, but also the formation of new models of Jewish masculinity. The creation of a «new Jew» who was physically and moral healthy was intended to encourage general regeneration, the rebirth of the nation, and accumulation of strength for the building of an independent state. 	</p>
		<p>The ideological founder of national Jewish gymnastics was Max Nordau, one of the co-organizers of the Zionist movement. At the congress of Worldwide Zionist Organizations in Basel in 1898 and 1901 Nordau spoke about the historical importance of forming a «new Jewishness» on the principles of so-called «muscular Judaism.» In contrast to anti-Semitic propaganda, where Jews were depicted as oppressed and weak, a new image of the Jew was necessary, the prototype of which was Bar Kokhba—the hero of the Jewish liberation movement in Roman times. His name itself became the name of the first Jewish gymnastics association founded in Berlin in 1898. On the model of the German gymnastics societies (turnverein) and the Slavic Sokol groups, there arose a network of societies called the «Maccabees.» In Galicia the centers of the gymnastics movements were in Lviv and Krakow. On the eve of World War I in Galicia there were 27 Jewish clubs with 2776 members.</p>
